params.name: images
params.description: Image to preprocess. Expects a single or batch of images.

params.name: header_text
params.description: Text to render as a header. Only has an effect if image_processor.is_vqa is True.

params.name: do_convert_rgb
params.description: Whether to convert the image to RGB.

params.name: max_patches
params.description: Maximum number of patches to extract.

params.name: patch_size
params.description: Dictionary containing the patch height and width.

params.name: return_tensors
params.description: The type of tensors to return. Can be one of:Unset: Return a list of np.ndarray.TensorType.TENSORFLOW or tf: Return a batch of type tf.Tensor.TensorType.PYTORCH or pt: Return a batch of type torch.Tensor.TensorType.NUMPY or np: Return a batch of type np.ndarray.TensorType.JAX or jax: Return a batch of type jax.numpy.ndarray.

params.name: data_format
params.description: The channel dimension format for the output image. Can be one of:channels_first or ChannelDimension.FIRST: image in (num_channels, height, width) format.channels_last or ChannelDimension.LAST: image in (height, width, num_channels) format.Unset: Use the channel dimension format of the input image.

params.name: input_data_format
params.description: The channel dimension format for the input image. If unset, the channel dimension format is inferredfrom the input image. Can be one of:channels_first or ChannelDimension.FIRST: image in (num_channels, height, width) format.channels_last or ChannelDimension.LAST: image in (height, width, num_channels) format.none or ChannelDimension.NONE: image in (height, width) format.
